djective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Malby was born about 1242, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of William Malby. She had at least 3 sons with Adam Conyers."},"et":{"abt 1242–":"umbes 1242–Surnud","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1240–1277":"1240–1277","1264–1315":"1264–1315","1266–1311":"1266–1311","1267–Male":"1267–Surnud","1217–Male":"1217–Surnud","1217":"1217","1315":"1315","1267":"1267","1311":"1311","1266":"1266","1277":"1277","Abt 1264":"umbes 1264","1264":"1264","1242":"1242","1240":"1240","about 1267":"umbes 1267","abt 1242":"umbes 1242","Wold Newton, East Riding of Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wold Newton, Yorkshire East Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Finningham, Suffolk, England":"Finningham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Ormesby, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Haton Conyers, Yorks, Eng":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1242–":"noin 1242–Kuollut","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1240–1277":"1240–1277","1264–1315":"1264–1315","1266–1311":"1266–1311","1267–Male":"1267–Kuollut","1217–Male":"1217–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1315":"1315","1267":"1267","1311":"1311","1266":"1266","1277":"1277","Abt 1264":"noin 1264","1264":"1264","1242":"1242","1240":"1240","about 1267":"noin 1267","abt 1242":"noin 1242","Wold Newton, East Riding of Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"